CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1946, pg. 1, reads: "Ready to Take Over - Ready to move in and take over, little Robert Pappy Williams, son of Magistrate and Mrs. Robert (Pappy) Williams of Webster Avenue, typifies the new year, 1947, which will be with us in [illegible] more days. - Harris photo."Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, National edition, January 4, 1947, pg. 11, reads: "'I'll Take it From Here' - And little Robert (Pappy) Williams looks the man for the job. 'Sir 1947' is the son of Magistrate and Mrs. Robert Williams of Pittsburgh. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Robert E. Williams Jr. in diaper and top hat standing on table in front of curtain, with mother Alberta Russell Williams on left
